u,Mold,Flintshire,Wales":"Mold, Flintshire, Wales"},"cs":{"1524–":"1524–Zesnulý","–Female":"Zesnulá","1524–Female":"1524–Zesnulá","1305–1365":"1305–1365","–Male":"Zesnulý","1524–Male":"1524–Zesnulý","1305":"1305","1524":"1524","1365":"1365","Abt 1546":"okolo 1546","Wales":"Wales","Gwernafield, Mold, Flintshire, Wales":"Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of Gwysanau,Mold,Flintshire,Wales":"Mold, Flintshire, Wales"},"da":{"1524–":"1524–Afdød","–Female":"Afdød","1524–Female":"1524–Afdød","1305–1365":"1305–1365","–Male":"Afdød","1524–Male":"1524–Afdød","1305":"1305","1524":"1524","1365":"1365","Abt 1546":"omkring 1546","Wales":"Wales","Gwernafield, Mold, Flintshire, Wales":"Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of Gwysanau,Mold,Flintshire,Wales":"Mold, Flintshire, Wales"},"nl":{"1524–":"1524–Overleden","–Female":"Overleden","1524–Female":"1524–Overleden","1305–1365":"1305–1365","–Male":"Overleden","1524–Male":"1524–Overleden","1305":"1305","1524":"1524","1365":"1365","Abt 1546":"circa 1546","Wales":"Wales","Gwernafield, Mold, Flintshire, Wales":"Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Gwysanau,Mold,Flintshire,Wales":"Mold, Flintshire, Wales"},"en":{"1524–":"1524–Deceased","–Female":"Deceased","1524–Female":"1524–Deceased","1305–1365":"1305–1365","–Male":"Deceased","1524–Male":"1524–Deceased","1305":"1305","1524":"1524","1365":"1365","Abt 1546":"about 1546","Wales":"Wales","Gwernafield, Mold, Flintshire, Wales":"Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of Gwysanau,Mold,Flintshire,Wales":"Mold, Flintshire, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert ap Hywel was born in 1524, in Mold, Flintshire, Wales. He married Margred Verch Ieuan about 1546, in Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1524–":"1524–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1524–Female":"1524–Surnud","1305–1365":"1305–1365","–Male":"Surnud","1524–Male":"1524–Surnud","1305":"1305","1524":"1524","1365":"1365","Abt 1546":"umbes 1546","Wales":"Wales","Gwernafield, Mold, Flintshire, Wales":"Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, United Kingdom","of Gwysanau,Mold,Flintshire,Wales":"Mold, Flintshire, Wales"},"fi":{"1524–":"1524–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1524–Female":"1524–Kuollut","1305–1365":"1305–1365","–Male":"Kuollut","1524–Male":"1524–Kuollut","1305":"1305","1524":"1524","1365":"1365","Abt 1546":"noin 1546","Wales":"Wales","Gwernafield, Mold, Flintshire, Wales":"Gwernafield, Flintshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuninga